The paper discusses the development of a theory for dealing with uncertain and imprecise sources of information, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The focus on artificial reasoning suggests that cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the combination of sources of information, which is relevant to machine learning and data science, suggesting cs.LG and cs.DS as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the foundations of the theory, which could be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SI).
